content.protection:
The route is protected with 11 bolts (12 if you include the anchor for

Early Warning

) and a 2-bolt anchor with chains and biners.

8 bolts to a 2-bolt anchor with chains and steel carabiners (the same anchors as for

Close Call

).

content.description:
Begin up the west side of the north face of Half & Half crag using varied grips to climb upward on increasingly harder terrain (note: after climbing past bolt 7 you will pass the 2-bolt anchor for

Close Call

). As you pass the left side of the highest roof, you encounter the crux, which is a steep section that requires technical face climbing. This transitions to easier climbing that leads to the anchors. From the anchors on Direct Hit, with a 60m rope, you can lower or rap and just reach the base of the climb.

The climbing on Close Call starts with easy scrambling to the first bolt followed by easy slab climbing until reaching the crux, which involves passing the large roof on its left side (do not wander left toward

Direct Hit

). The face climbing above trends to the right and joins the left-facing crack which leads to the anchors.
